HIS-element assets

This directory contains genome-wide HIS-element annotations for five grass species:

HIS-element_Bdistachyon.tar.gz
HIS-element_MH63.tar.gz
HIS-element_Sbicolor.tar.gz
HIS-element_Sitalica.tar.gz
HIS-element_Zmays.tar.gz

Each archive contains tissue-level BED files of HIS-elements for the corresponding species.

File organization
Each BED file represents one tissue or sample.
File/sample IDs correspond to the entries in the root-directory _sample.txt file.
Users can identify the tissue represented by each BED file by matching its file ID to _sample.txt.
Coordinate systems

Please use the correct reference genome assembly when visualizing these BED files.

Brachypodium distachyon: Bd21-3 v1.1
Rice: MSU7.0 coordinate system for HIS-element BED files
Setaria italica: v2.0
Sorghum bicolor: v3.1.1
Zea mays: AGPv4

Important note for rice:
The rice deep-learning model was trained on MH63RS2, but the rice HIS-element coordinates provided here are reported in the MSU7.0 genome coordinate system, consistent with the cCRE annotation framework used in the manuscript.

Reference genome and annotation sources

Please download the matching genome FASTA file before loading BED tracks into IGV.
If you want to display gene structures, also download the corresponding annotation file (GFF3/GTF).

